Arrow functions
-------------------------
It is a short syntax for defining anonymous functions.
It si also known as lambda function.

syntax:
-----------
( with or without parameters) => expression


//arrow function without any parameter
let message=()=>{
console.log("welcome to arrow functions");
}
message();

//arrow function with one parameter
let display=(fname:string)=>{
console.log("name is ",fname);
}
display("srinivas");

//arrow function with two parameters
let result=(num1:number,num2:number) => {
console.log("total is "+(num1+num2));
}
result(67,65);

//arrow function with two parameters and with return type.
let sum=(num1:number, num2:number):number =>{
return num1+num2;
}
console.log(sum(4,5));